    "seguidores": 21700,
    "bio": "Award-Winning Career Coach 🏆\nHelping women land $150K+ roles\nAuthor of Authentic Success\n💌 kate@shatteredglasscoaching.com\nBook your free call 👇🏼",
    "descripcion": "Being a hard worker isn’t enough. You need to be seen as strategic, instead. \n\n\"Hardworking\" is the participation trophy of leadership. The default thing people say about a woman when they can't think of anything more strategic.\n\nAt the more senior level of your career, you can’t JUST be known as hard-working. You need to be seen as strategic leader.\n\nHow to be seen as a strategic leader:\n→ Stop talking about effort. Start talking about thinking. \"I worked late on it\" becomes \"Here's how I approached it.\"\n→ Share your opinions in meetings. What are your takes on what the company should do?\n→ Get visible on the work that matters. Not operational work, but strategic work. \n→ Stop being grateful for opportunities. Start being clear about which opportunities you want.\n→ Stop saying \"happy to help.\" Strategic leaders are clear about priorities, not what they're willing to take on.\n\nHardworking served you earlier in your career. Being strategic is what gets you to the next level.\n\n#careeradvice #careergrowth #careerdevelopment #careeradvancement #careercoach ",
